Mirroring or redistributing the original software on other platforms or websites without the explicit written permission of the author is STRICTLY PROHIBITED.

## 2. Modifications and Forks

You ARE ALLOWED to create forks and modified versions of McBackuper, provided that:

- The modified version is NOT sold or distributed under the name "McBackuper" (see Section 3: Trademark).
- You provide a prominent notice stating that the software is a modified derivative of the original McBackuper.
- You include a link back to the official source repository.
- Your fork's code is NOT intended to facilitate illegal activities or bypass security measures.

Violation of this section automatically terminates your right to use or modify any part of the McBackuper code.

## 3. Trademark and Naming

The name "McBackuper" is a trademark of Art_Farm.
- You may not use the name "McBackuper" for your forks or derivative works.
- Suggested naming for forks: "[Your Name]'s backup tool, based on McBackuper".

## 4. Non-Commercial Use

Forks and original source code may not be used for commercial resale without a separate, written agreement with the author.
